# Cairn — environment. Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored.
#
# Anything prefixed EXPO_PUBLIC_ is INLINED INTO THE JS BUNDLE and is readable
# by anyone with the app. Only put values there that are designed to be public.
# Everything without that prefix is build-time only and never reaches a device.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase  —  https://supabase.com/dashboard  →  Project Settings → API
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Project URL, e.g. https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=

# The `anon` / publishable key. Public by design: every table is default-deny
# under RLS and all reads go through security-definer RPCs.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# service_role key — BYPASSES RLS COMPLETELY. Anyone holding it can read and
# write every row and every storage object in the project, ignoring every policy.
#
# READ BY EXACTLY ONE THING: the server-side route `app/api/audio+api.ts`, which
# runs on the Metro dev server (and only there) and uses it to mint 60-second
# signed URLs for `cairn-audio` — but only after re-running `cairn_detail` as the
# calling user and confirming the proximity gate returned band = 'unlocked'.
#
# THE PREFIX IS THE WHOLE SAFETY PROPERTY. This name has NO `EXPO_PUBLIC_`, and
# adding one would not "make it work" — it would inline the key into the JS
# bundle and ship a full RLS bypass to every device that opens the app. If you
# ever find yourself typing EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, stop; the
# thing that is broken is something else.
#
# Dashboard → Project Settings → API Keys → `service_role` / `secret`. See
# supabase/SETUP.md, "Audio signing". Leave blank and audio playback returns a
# 501 naming this variable; nothing else is affected.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ElevenLabs Scribe  —  speech-to-text (CRN-022)
#   https://elevenlabs.io/app/settings/api-keys
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# SERVER-ONLY, exactly like the service_role key above. Read by
# `app/api/transcribe+api.ts` and by nothing else. NO `EXPO_PUBLIC_` PREFIX, and
# adding one does not "make it work" — it inlines a billable key into the JS
# bundle, where anyone with the app can pull it out and spend it.
#
# Why a hosted API at all, when transcription could run free and offline on the
# phone: Slovenian. It is not a supported locale on SFSpeechRecognizer (64) or
# on iOS 26's SpeechTranscriber (42), so Apple's on-device speech cannot read
# the audio recorded at this hackathon at all. Scribe can. That is the entire
# reason — see tracker/reference/on-device-ai.md, and do not reopen it today.
#
# Leave blank and the transcribe route returns a 501 naming this variable.
# Nothing else is affected: stones still record, upload, appear on the map and
# play, and `stones.transcript` simply stays null, which the UI renders as
# audio-only with no spinner and no placeholder.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Mapbox  —  https://account.mapbox.com/access-tokens/
#
# TWO TOKENS. TWO DIFFERENT JOBS. THEY ARE NOT INTERCHANGEABLE.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. PUBLIC token, starts `pk.`  —  RUNTIME.
#    Passed to Mapbox.setAccessToken() before the first MapView mounts.
#    Safe to ship in the bundle; that is what public tokens are for.
EXPO_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# 2. SECRET token, starts `sk.`, scope DOWNLOADS:READ  —  BUILD TIME ONLY.
#    CocoaPods uses it during `pod install` to fetch the Mapbox native SDK from
#    Mapbox's private registry. It has NO runtime use. It is read by
#    app.config.ts and handed to the @rnmapbox/maps config plugin.
#
#    Create it at account.mapbox.com → Create a token → tick DOWNLOADS:READ.
#    It is shown EXACTLY ONCE. Paste it here before you close that tab.
#
#    A `401 Unauthorized` during pod install means this is missing, mistyped,
#    or lacks DOWNLOADS:READ. It is never a network problem and re-running
#    does not help.
MAPBOX_DOWNLOAD_TOKEN=

# 3. OPTIONAL style URL  —  RUNTIME. Not a secret.
#    A PUBLISHED Mapbox Studio style, `mapbox://styles/<user>/<styleid>`.
#    Leave this blank and the app uses the contour style built into
#    src/map/cairnStyle.ts — which needs no Studio account and cannot hit the
#    "unpublished draft renders blank on someone else's device" trap.
#    Set it only to override. Changing it requires `npx expo start --clear`,
#    because EXPO_PUBLIC_* values are inlined into the bundle at build time.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_STYLE_URL=

# Optional: @rnmapbox/maps v10 also reads the download token from this variable
# directly, which is the non-deprecated path. Set EITHER this OR the one above.
# Setting both works but prints a deprecation warning during prebuild.
# RNMAPBOX_MAPS_DOWNLOAD_TOKEN=
